        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Claude: add session usage + weekly pace menu bar metric",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds the combined **session usage + weekly pace** menu-bar metric option to the **Claude** provider, mirroring the existing Codex `Session + Weekly` option. The menu bar shows the 5-hour session and weekly lanes together (e.g. `5h 12% ôñ W 45%` in percent mode) and paces on the weekly lane in pace/both modes.\n\nPreviously this combined option was gated to Codex only (`menuBarMetricSupportsPrimaryAndSecondary == .codex`), so Claude's *Menu bar metric* picker only offered Automatic / Primary (Session) / Secondary (Weekly) ã even though Claude already exposes both lanes in its data, dual-lane icon, and dropdown rows.\n\nTo use it: **Preferences ã Providers ã Claude ã Menu bar metric ã Session + Weekly**.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Enable `.primaryAndSecondary` for Claude (`SettingsStore+MenuPreferences`), which surfaces the picker option, persistence, and read-back.\n- Render the combined menu-bar text and weekly pace for Claude (`StatusItemController+Animation`).\n- Rename the now-shared helper `MenuBarDisplayText.codexCombinedPercentText` ã `combinedSessionWeeklyPercentText` (and `codexSessionLabel` ã `sessionWindowLabel`), since it is no longer Codex-specific.\n- Extend the \"show highest usage\" merged-icon exclusion for the combined metric to Claude (`UsageStore+HighestUsage`).\n- Changelog entry under 0.37.3.\n\n## Correctness note\n\nClaude's OAuth usage can omit `five_hour`; in that case the existing mapper parks the 7-day window in **both** `primary` and `secondary`. A naive port would mislabel that as a session lane and render `168h 42% ôñ W 42%`. The combined path therefore classifies lanes by **window cadence** (only a 300-minute window counts as the session lane), so a weekly-only account correctly shows `W 42%`. Codex keeps resolving its lanes through its consumer projection, unchanged.\n\n## Tests\n\nAdded coverage for: the picker option appearing for Claude, the combined display (`5h 12% ôñ W 45%`), the weekly-only fallback (`W 42%`), pace mode (weekly lane), and highest-usage ranking (one lane vs both lanes exhausted). `make check` is clean (0 lint violations); all directly-affected suites pass and the project builds in release.\n\nÞÊ Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
